-- CDR Financial’s David Rubin Pleads Guilty in Municipal Bid Rigging Case
-- B y   B o b   V a n   V o r i s
-- 2011-12-30T17:56:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-30/cdr-financial-s-david-rubin-pleads-guilty-in-municipal-bid-rigging-case.html
CDR Financial Products Inc.’s David
Rubin is set to plead guilty today in Manhattan federal court, a
court clerk said.  Rubin, the founder of  Beverly Hills , California-based CDR,
and two other employees are charged along with the company as
part of an investigation into bid- and auction-rigging in the
municipal  bond market . Rubin, the firm’s former chief financial
officer, took kickbacks for running sham auctions for the
investments, prosecutors said. All pleaded not guilty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Van Voris in New York at 
